            The F-15D the two seat version of the F-15, a high-performance, supersonic, allweather air-superiority fighter built by McDonnell
            Douglas Aerospace powered by two Pratt and Whitney F-100 turbofan engines. Its primary mission is aerial combat. This model does not support ground missions.
            Radar and heat seeking air-to-air missiles and a 20 MM gun are the primary armament. 
            MTOW 74,350 lbs. VNE 1100. Max Gear extension 300 kts. Max Flap speed 250kts.
